<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 14:32:10 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>想避免挑食吗？尽早让您的孩子接触蔬菜——在子宫里</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/want-to-avoid-having-a-picky-eater-start-exposing-your-kids-to-veggies-super-early-in-the-womb-180988750/</link><description>在一项新的研究中，在胎儿时期反复接触苦羽衣甘蓝味道的 3 岁儿童似乎对绿叶蔬菜的气味的反感程度不如对子宫内未曾体验过的食物气味的反感程度。</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/want-to-avoid-having-a-picky-eater-start-exposing-your-kids-to-veggies-super-early-in-the-womb-180988750/</guid></item><item><title>考古学家称，一名妇女被埋在精致的罗马棺材中，棺材里还装有珍贵的陪葬品，“显然她的家人和社区都非常珍惜她”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-woman-buried-in-an-elaborate-roman-coffin-with-precious-grave-goods-was-clearly-cherished-by-her-family-and-her-community-archaeologists-say-180988760/</link><description>英国科尔切斯特是罗马不列颠的第一个首都所在地，一场新展览探索了“莱克斯登女士”和她的珍宝收藏</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 13:41:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-woman-buried-in-an-elaborate-roman-coffin-with-precious-grave-goods-was-clearly-cherished-by-her-family-and-her-community-archaeologists-say-180988760/</guid></item><item><title>马德里这座教堂的令人惊叹的壁画进行了整容——但埋在壁画下面的西班牙艺术家的头仍然不见了</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/stunning-frescoes-in-this-madrid-church-received-a-facelift-but-goya-the-spanish-artist-buried-beneath-them-is-still-missing-his-head-180988756/</link><description>戈雅的壁画在西班牙的一座教堂中获得了新的生命，这座教堂也是戈雅大部分遗体的最后安息之地。他失踪的头骨之谜激发了诗歌和艺术作品的灵感</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 20:10:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/stunning-frescoes-in-this-madrid-church-received-a-facelift-but-goya-the-spanish-artist-buried-beneath-them-is-still-missing-his-head-180988756/</guid></item><item><title>世界卫生组织宣布非洲埃博拉疫情为全球卫生紧急事件。以下是关于罕见但严重的疾病的知识</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-ebola-outbreak-in-africa-was-declared-a-global-health-emergency-by-the-who-heres-what-to-know-about-the-rare-but-severe-illness-180988758/</link><description>国际卫生机构指出，此次疫情不符合大流行标准，美国疾病控制与预防中心表示，美国公众面临的风险较低</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 19:16:20 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-ebola-outbreak-in-africa-was-declared-a-global-health-emergency-by-the-who-heres-what-to-know-about-the-rare-but-severe-illness-180988758/</guid></item><item><title>这位摄影师以拍摄玛丽莲·梦露等名人而闻名，但他拍摄的越南战争受害者和煤矿工人的照片揭示了肖像的惊人力量</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/richard-avedon-was-famous-for-snapping-celebrities-like-marilyn-monroe-but-his-images-of-vietnam-war-victims-and-coal-miners-revealed-the-surprising-power-of-portraits-180988757/</link><description>一部关于摄影师理查德·阿维登 (Richard Avedon) 的新纪录片由朗·霍华德 (Ron Howard) 执导，在戛纳电影节首映，利用档案镜头和当代采访来讲述他的影​​响力到底有多大</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 18:46:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/richard-avedon-was-famous-for-snapping-celebrities-like-marilyn-monroe-but-his-images-of-vietnam-war-victims-and-coal-miners-revealed-the-surprising-power-of-portraits-180988757/</guid></item><item><title>在西澳大利亚的一个洞穴中发现的带有酒窝的考拉化石揭示了这种以前未知的物种灭绝的原因</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/dimpled-koala-fossil-found-western-australia-revealed-why-previously-unknown-species-died-out-180988719/</link><description>这项新研究发现，由于气候干燥，它们失去了树栖栖息地，这对面临类似威胁的现代有袋动物来说是一个可怕的警告</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 18:17:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/dimpled-koala-fossil-found-western-australia-revealed-why-previously-unknown-species-died-out-180988719/</guid></item><item><title>昆虫能感觉到疼痛吗？新研究表明蟋蟀确实如此</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/can-insects-feel-pain-new-research-suggests-that-crickets-do-180988752/</link><description>这些生物用于食物、饲料和研究，是养殖最广泛的昆虫之一。研究作者表示，人类应该努力减少昆虫养殖、处理和实验中的危害</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 16:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/can-insects-feel-pain-new-research-suggests-that-crickets-do-180988752/</guid></item><item><title>随着华盛顿地标建筑继续庆祝其成立 50 周年，这些色彩缤纷的当代艺术品加入了赫希霍恩博物馆的收藏</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-colorful-contemporary-artworks-just-joined-the-hirshhorn-museum-as-the-dc-landmark-celebrated-its-50th-anniversary-180988749/</link><description>该博物馆还准备于今年秋天重新开放其重新设计的雕塑花园，展出八位艺术家的新作品</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 15:00:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-colorful-contemporary-artworks-just-joined-the-hirshhorn-museum-as-the-dc-landmark-celebrated-its-50th-anniversary-180988749/</guid></item><item><title>座头鲸有时会无缘无故地张开嘴。游客正在帮助科学家了解这种罕见的行为</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/humpback-whales-sometimes-hold-their-mouths-open-for-no-clear-reason-tourists-are-helping-scientists-understand-the-rare-behavior-180988743/</link><description>从社交媒体收集的大量照片和视频帮助研究人员提出了这种很少被记录的动作（称为“张开嘴”）的一些可能原因，包括沟通、下巴伸展和玩耍</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/humpback-whales-sometimes-hold-their-mouths-open-for-no-clear-reason-tourists-are-helping-scientists-understand-the-rare-behavior-180988743/</guid></item><item><title>碧昂斯和泰勒·斯威夫特的音乐以及数十首其他“音频宝藏”已添加到国家唱片登记处</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/music-from-taylor-swift-and-beyonce-plus-dozens-of-other-audio-treasures-added-to-national-recording-registry-180988754/</link><description>美国国会图书馆国家播放列表中最新添加的 25 首歌曲被认为“因其在国家录制的声音遗产中的文化、历史或美学重要性而值得永远保存”</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 21:32:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/music-from-taylor-swift-and-beyonce-plus-dozens-of-other-audio-treasures-added-to-national-recording-registry-180988754/</guid></item><item><title>在巨大的铁器时代宝藏中发现了英国部落强大女王可能使用过的“神奇”镜子，目前正在展出</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-magical-mirror-the-powerful-queen-of-a-british-tribe-may-have-used-goes-on-display-as-part-of-britains-largest-iron-age-hoard-180988751/</link><description>参观约克郡博物馆的游客可以看到来自梅尔森比宝库的文物，其历史可以追溯到公元一世纪，这些文物改写了罗马入侵时期英国财富和权力的故事</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 20:44:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-magical-mirror-the-powerful-queen-of-a-british-tribe-may-have-used-goes-on-display-as-part-of-britains-largest-iron-age-hoard-180988751/</guid></item><item><title>无意识意识是否意识到周围的环境？新研究表明麻醉大脑可以处理无意中听到的单词</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/is-the-unconscious-mind-aware-of-its-surroundings-new-research-suggests-anesthetized-brains-can-process-overheard-words-180988710/</link><description>七名参与者的电极暂时植入对学习很重要的大脑结构中。在麻醉状态下，他们的神经细胞学会了区分不同的声音，甚至可以预测短语中即将出现的单词</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 15:40:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/is-the-unconscious-mind-aware-of-its-surroundings-new-research-suggests-anesthetized-brains-can-process-overheard-words-180988710/</guid></item><item><title>新的稀有鸽子幼崽是已灭绝野生鸟类的“希望之源”，也是拯救它们的雄心勃勃的计划向前迈出的一步</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-rare-dove-hatchlings-are-a-source-of-hope-for-the-extinct-in-the-wild-birds-and-a-step-forward-in-the-ambitious-project-to-save-them-180988730/</link><description>自 1972 年以来，索科罗斑鸠就没有在野外记录过，但环保人士表示，由于长期的重新引入努力，这种情况可能会在几年内发生变化</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 15:07:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-rare-dove-hatchlings-are-a-source-of-hope-for-the-extinct-in-the-wild-birds-and-a-step-forward-in-the-ambitious-project-to-save-them-180988730/</guid></item><item><title>一名男子在泰国的一个池塘附近发现了奇怪的岩石。它们原来是一种巨大的新恐龙物种的骨头</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-man-spotted-strange-looking-rocks-near-a-pond-in-thailand-they-turned-out-to-be-the-bones-of-a-massive-new-dinosaur-species-180988744/</link><description>古生物学家将这种长颈食草生物称为“Nagatitan chaiyaphumensis”。这是泰国第 14 种被命名的恐龙，它可能是东南亚迄今为止发现的最大的恐龙</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-man-spotted-strange-looking-rocks-near-a-pond-in-thailand-they-turned-out-to-be-the-bones-of-a-massive-new-dinosaur-species-180988744/</guid></item><item><title>尼安德特人也有蛀牙，新的研究表明他们会像现代牙医一样钻进牙齿来治疗蛀牙</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/neanderthals-got-cavities-too-and-new-research-suggests-they-drilled-into-their-teeth-to-treat-them-just-like-modern-dentists-180988746/</link><description>研究人员出土了一颗 59,000 年前的尼安德特人臼齿，它显示出牙科手术的迹象，这一发现将最早的牙科手术证据推迟了大约 45,000 年</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 13:34:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/neanderthals-got-cavities-too-and-new-research-suggests-they-drilled-into-their-teeth-to-treat-them-just-like-modern-dentists-180988746/</guid></item><item><title>弗里达·卡洛 (Frida Kahlo) 和迭戈·里维拉 (Diego Rivera) 在受希腊神话和墨西哥魔幻现实主义启发的大都会歌剧院中自唱至死</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/frida-kahlo-and-diego-rivera-sing-themselves-to-death-in-an-opera-at-the-met-inspired-by-greek-mythology-and-mexican-magical-realism-180988742/</link><description>全新制作的全西班牙歌剧《El Último Sueño de Frida y Diego》本周在纽约上演，而现代艺术博物馆的合作展览则探讨了这部歌剧背后的艺术</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 20:23:20 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/frida-kahlo-and-diego-rivera-sing-themselves-to-death-in-an-opera-at-the-met-inspired-by-greek-mythology-and-mexican-magical-realism-180988742/</guid></item><item><title>最新研究表明，这种鱼会搭在蝠鲼的“屁眼”上</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-fish-hitches-rides-in-manta-rays-buttholes-according-to-new-research-180988736/</link><description>科学家怀疑这种行为可能会伤害蝠鲼，这表明鲳鱼与其宿主之间存在复杂的关系，有时可能是寄生关系</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 19:56:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-fish-hitches-rides-in-manta-rays-buttholes-according-to-new-research-180988736/</guid></item><item><title>不开玩笑，梅尔·布鲁克斯在 100 岁生日之前将他的搞笑档案捐赠给国家喜剧中心</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/no-joke-ahead-of-his-100th-birthday-mel-brooks-donates-his-hilarious-archive-to-the-national-comedy-center-180988741/</link><description>属于“2000 岁老人”和 EGOT 获奖者的数千条笔记、故事板、早期脚本和照片将与露西尔·鲍尔、琼·里弗斯和乔治·卡林的材料一起加入</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 19:21:03 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/no-joke-ahead-of-his-100th-birthday-mel-brooks-donates-his-hilarious-archive-to-the-national-comedy-center-180988741/</guid></item><item><title>在白令海峡修建大坝能否使地球免受气候变化的影响？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-building-a-dam-across-the-bering-straight-save-the-planet-from-some-effects-of-climate-change-180988725/</link><description>一项初步研究表明，封锁俄罗斯和阿拉斯加之间的水道可能有助于关键洋流系统的生存。但可能会产生潜在的不可预见的后果，特别是对海洋生态系统</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 16:05:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-building-a-dam-across-the-bering-straight-save-the-planet-from-some-effects-of-climate-change-180988725/</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，胎儿在子宫内就可以从母亲那里“感染”哈欠</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/fetuses-can-catch-yawns-from-their-mothers-while-still-in-the-womb-new-research-suggests-180988735/</link><description>打哈欠被认为是一种社交行为。尽管众所周知胎儿会打哈欠，但科学家们不确定这是否是一种独立的反射，或者他们是否能以某种方式检测到来自母亲的暗示</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/fetuses-can-catch-yawns-from-their-mothers-while-still-in-the-womb-new-research-suggests-180988735/</guid></item></channel></rss>